headline: Why French prosecutors investigating X summoned Elon Musk
description: The French investigation that led to a raid on the Paris offices of X on Tuesday is examining a wide range of alleged offenses.

headline: Trump signs spending bill ending US government shutdown
Iran cracks down on medical workers treating protesters
Ukraine seeks countermeasures against Russian drones equipped with Starlink
description: A wave of highly accurate and deadly strikes on civilian and military targets far from the front lines has led the Ukrainian government to ask Elon Musk for help. Musk claims to have taken the necessary steps to disable Starlink terminals being used by the Russian military.

headline: French prosecutors request Le Pen's election ban be upheld
description: Last year, far-right party leader Marine Le Pen was convicted of embezzling EU Parliament funds. She is appealing against the conviction and the sentence that would ban her from running in the presidential election.

headline: IOC official says work on 2030 French Alps Winter Olympics is 'behind schedule'
description: The day before the announcement, the chair of the 2030 Winter Olympics organising team's compensation committee stepped down, becoming the third senior official to quit in just over two months.

headline: Gabriella Papadakis, ice dancer: 'My mother turned me into a little soldier who let herself be guided by the decisions of others'
description: 'I wouldn't be where I am today if...' In this series, Le Monde interviews a personality about a decisive moment in their life. The figure skater and former Olympic champion looks back on a childhood filled with constraints in order to succeed in a demanding and conservative environment.

headline: US jet downs Iran drone but talks still on course

France's 2026 budget battle is finally over. The next one may be even more complex.
description: The Finance Ministry is already working on the next budget bill. On paper, France will need to make a deficit reduction effort twice as great as in 2026. It will be a daunting challenge, so close to the presidential election.

headline: A bike journey across crisis-ridden Cuba under the watchful eye of state security
description: 'Cuba, an island adrift' (3/3). Le Monde reporters left Havana by bicycle to discover this country where people, under constant surveillance, have learned to survive through resourcefulness and the black market.

headline: Epstein case's poison spreads with release of new files
description: On January 30, the US Department of Justice released a new trove of documents related to the case of the sexual predator who died in prison in 2019. Far from clarifying the case's many gray areas, these files have only deepened the confusion.

headline: Thomas Piketty: 'European countries have achieved unprecedented levels of prosperity and social well-being'
